easypage-editor

1) Starting the Server
2) Development
3) Generating User Credentials


------------------------------------------------------------------------
Starting the Server

$ node . --port 1234 --site path/to/site.json --users path/to/users.json


------------------------------------------------------------------------
Development

You have to start the node server and gulp server in parallel.
$ node . --port 9002 --site ../demos/site.json --users ../demos/user.json
$ gulp build connect

Launch a webserver on http://localhost:9001 and login with user demo and
password demo.


------------------------------------------------------------------------
Generating User Credentials

$ node
> const crypto = require('crypto')
> crypto.createHmac('sha512', 'theUsername').update('thePassword').digest('hex')
